title: Bournemouth 0 - Man City 2: Worry over Jesus injury as Aguero takes centre stage
text:
1 of 10 Twitter reacts as Gabriel Jesus is forced off with injury against Bournemouth 
Aguero had little to do with Sterling's opener as Leroy Sane's flow cross was deflected up into the England international's path to tap home at the far post. 
But Aguero did get a toe in to force the second goal, in which the ball deflected off Mings and into the net. 
Bournemouth thought they were level seconds after Sterling's tap-in when Josh King found the net, only for referee Neil Swarbrick to bring back play for a shirt pull. REUTERS Sergio Aguero was keen to get on the field following Jesus' injury PA Aguero was benched for a third successive game REUTERS Gabriel Jesus (left) injured his foot after 14 minutes REUTERS Bournemouth's Jack Wilshere also came off injured 
The Cherries had their chances to get back into the game, while City should really have doubled their lead when Aguero smashed a volley wide of the mark from six yards. 
Sane himself hit the crossbar late on as City waltzed around their hosts playing keep-ball. 
And they are not the only ones coming out of the game with an injury worry as Jack Wilshere, on loan at Bournemouth from Arsenal, came off before half time with an ankle problem after an ineffectual 45 minutes in the middle of the park. Related articles
